{#
/**
 * @file
 * Suggestion-target passthrough for events-first group pages.  (#122 / SC-3)
 *
 * Resolved when groups_chrome_theme_suggestions_group_alter() appends
 * `group__community_group__events_first` (field_group_type = "Event
 * planning"). This template carries NO markup of its own — the three
 * suggestion variants (events/discussion/docs-first) differ ONLY in
 * preprocess-computed DATA (gc_group.lead_*), never in per-variant markup, so
 * duplicating the ~80 lines of header/tabs/lead-section markup three times
 * would triplicate a single source of truth for zero visual gain
 * (wireframe.md §4, decision (b)). The suggestion mechanism itself is the
 * thing this story's AC requires to exist — this file (and its two
 * siblings) is what makes that mechanism resolve to an actual template
 * instead of silently falling back to group--full.html.twig.
 *
 * @see groups_chrome_theme_suggestions_group_alter()
 * @see groups_chrome_preprocess_group()
 */
#}
